entry.title: Set FormFieldData::is_autofilled only on fills
entry.content:
Autofill used to set FormFieldData::is_autofilled whenever the

WebAutofillState was either kAutofilled or kPreviewed. This made the

browser not able to distinguish filled from previewed fields.



This issue causes problems in suggetions when they are triggered while

hovering over a previous suggestion (see linked bug for more details).

And even the the filling-after-broken-suggestions was also broken.



This CL fixes the issue by setting the boolean only for

WebAutofilState::kAutofilled. Note that now the browser cannot

distinguish between previewed and not filled fields, but that should

not be a problem.

entry.title: webview(metrics): Fix host package information in SDK runtime
entry.content:
The context we retrieve for the SDK runtime is a generic

sdksandbox context. This results in our metrics and minidumps

reporting a generic package name that won't help

for investigating issues.



The good news is that the uid for the SDK sandbox

process does belong to the host app and there is a deterministic

relationship between the SDK process and the host app

so we can get the host apps information from it.



The one tricky bit is that this trick doesn't apply to the

render process because it is an isolated process and so

doesn't have this same relationship.

We settled on feeding this through as a command line

switch.



I unfortunately haven't added tests because we don't

have any instrumentation tests for the SDK runtime

and this behavior is wildly environment specific.

I just tested it manually with a shell app that contains

a WebView and also confirmed that the mini dumps show

correctly in the dev UI when I induce a crash with

chrome://crash. I have also tested this against staging

crashpad and confirmed that the crashes show up there.



Low-Coverage-Reason: We don't have Rb infrastructure for tests

Motion blur cursor has been broken:

(1) It crashes because it tries to access fast ink host before

it's set

(2) When enabling motion blur cursor, it would get stuck at a black

correctly.

(5) It also gets a low-quality cursor image because it draws on

a scaled canvas.



This CL fixes the above issues.

entry.title: dlp: Run progress cb after resuming CopyOrMove
entry.content:
Runs the progress_callback_ in CopyOrMoveIOTaskPolicyImpl just before

starting the transfer. This ensures that if the task was paused and

resumed, the progress is updated after resuming and not only after the

first file is successfully copied or moved as is the case now.



This is especially important when the CopyOrMove task is part of a

RestoreToDestinationIOTask, which listens to progress updates from its

underlying move task to set its own state to the correct one. Without

the additional update, the Restore task would stay "paused" until the

first file is restored and only switch to "InProgress" if there are

more files left (otherwise to "Completed"). If this first file is very

large, we could potentially have a long period of time in which the

states of the two tasks, Resume and Move, don't match and could lead

to bugs, e.g. if we show another warning for the "paused" task.



R=chromeos-dlp@google.com, lucmult@chromium.org

handle it.

entry.title: Add DataConsumePolicy to ServiceWorkerRaceNetworkRequestURLLoaderClient
entry.content:
This is a refactoring CL to simplify the redirect handling in

BestEffortServiceWorker.



Currently, the network request, which is triggered by

BestEffortServiceWorker or ServiceWorkerAutoPreload, doesn't handle the

redirect, and ask the fetch handler to handle it instead. This behavior

was introduced in crrev.com/c/4680667



Before this CL, that behavior is achieved by setting

|FetchResponseFrom::kServiceWorker| in OnReceiveRedirect(), and do not

start teeing response in OnReceiveResponse() when

|FetchResponseFrom::kServiceWorker| is already set.



However, this behavior will be confusing once we land

ServiceWorkerAutoPreload behavior. Because ServiceWorkerAutoPreload is

going to set |FetchResponseFrom::kServiceWorker| in advance, as it

always uses the response from the fetch handler.



After this CL, whether the response data is tee-ed or not is determined

by the new member called `data_consume_policy_`. This is an enum that

specifies tee-ed or not. The default is kTeeResponse, which indicates

teeing data. When a redirect happens, kForwardingOnly is set. That

indicates the response data is only forwarded to the pipe for the fetch

handler, just for the preload/dedupe purpose.

entry.title: Use GetNetworkConnectivityHint for network change notifier
entry.content:
On Windows 10 Build 19041 the GetNetworkConnectivityHint API

provides better and more reliable information about the network

state.



This CL changes the code to use this API instead of using

the older WSALookupServiceBegin API.



GetNetworkConnectivityHint API also works inside App Container

sandbox.



Note: This CL does not fix other issues with network list

determination which are contained in crbug.com/1469771.



This CL also bumps the minimum version for Network sandbox

to Windows 10 Build 19041 to match support for this API. The number

of clients between RS5 and 20H1 is small, so should not affect

sandbox support to a large degree.



This CL also adds a test that the network change notifier works

inside Windows sandbox. The new test dynamically adds a new

adapter to the host, and verifies that a network change

notification is sent from the network service to the browser

process. This test also verifies that the new network adapter can

successfully be enumerated.



BUG=1450754

entry.title: Revert "service worker: ServiceWorkerContextWrapper to maintain browser context"
entry.content:
This reverts commit b53126e0ddd699682d688e18dd1f5aa18aec69a3.



Reason for revert: Causing consistent test failures on Linux Tests (Wayland) builder

i.e. https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20Tests%20(Wayland)/41977/test-results?sortby=&groupby=



Original change's description:

> service worker: ServiceWorkerContextWrapper to maintain browser context

>

> This CL makes ServiceWorkerContextWrapper to maintain the browser

> context by itself rather than having the dependency of

> ServiceWorkerProcessManager. This is to avoid the complication when

> destroying its own members. For example, ServiceWorkerContextCore

> requires a valid browser context during destruction and

> ServiceWorkerContextWrapper ends up needing to be careful on the

> sequence of shutting down ServiceWorkerProcessManager and destroying

> ServiceWorkerContextCore.
